## How to read this

- **Values** are case-sensitive. `happy` and `Happy` are different.
- **Per-character** sections list values valid for that character
  only. A mood that works for Jean may not work for Rogue.
- **Unknown values** produce a compile error with the full list, so
  even without this cheatsheet you find your way back.

## Parenthetical slots

Positional order when writing without keys:

```
(mood, face, arms, look, outfit, stage)
```

Named-only slots (no positional slot):
`left_arm`, `right_arm`, `pose`.

Reserved value: `text` (on its own, switches the line to phone-text
medium; mutually exclusive with visual attributes).

Positional-skip token: `_` (skips the slot without changing it).

## Speakers

Valid speaker names for dialogue blocks. Use the `UPPERCASE` form as
the line prefix in a `.scene` file, and refer to the same character
in `[[if]]` expressions and interpolations with the PascalCase form.

