## Engine effects (FX)

Source: `_allowlists/fx.yaml` (manual). These are Python effect
functions — visual or transient (phone shake, knock overlay, bamf
flash, …), distinct from sound files. Called with
`[[fx name(...)]]`; parentheses required even when empty;
positional args only.

See `scenes_source/_allowlists/fx.yaml` for the authoritative list
and signatures. The common ones: `phone_buzz()`, `knock_on_door()`,
`bamf()`, `smack()`, `crack()`, `pow_effect()`.

