## Title page keys

Source: hardcoded in the format (not an allowlist).

| Key | Required | Type | Meaning |
|---|---|---|---|
| `Title` | Yes | string | Human-readable title |
| `Scene Id` | Yes | snake_case | Becomes the label name |
| `Character` | Yes | PascalCase | Owning character |
| `Scene Type` | Yes | `cinematic` / `phone` / `texting` / `hub_option` | Compilation target |
| `Trigger` | For `cinematic` only | enum | `manual`, `sleeping`, `waking`, `traveling`, `getting_ready_for_bed`, or a mod-prefixed flag. Other scene types default to `manual` if omitted. |
| `Description` | No | string | One-line summary, helpful for the dev. Preserved when migrating from legacy JSON. |
| `Conditions` | No | expression | Ren'Py condition, comma-joined clauses become `and` |
| `Priority` | No | int | Event priority, default 50 |
| `Repeatable` | No | bool | Default `false` |
| `Tags` | No | comma list | Extra flags on the event |
| `Location` | No | slugline text | Implied opening slugline |
| `Openness` | For `phone` only | enum | `open`, `steady` |
| `Stage` | For `phone` only | string | `early`, `middle`, `late`, `showing`, `due` |
| `Format` | No | int | Format version override, default 1 |

### Body comments

Lines whose first non-whitespace character is `#` are comments —
stripped at compile time, invisible at runtime. Use them to annotate
a scene for other authors or the dev.

`#` appearing in the middle of a regular line is **not** a comment
(it's treated as prose).

HTML-style `<!-- … -->` comments are **not** supported and produce a
compile error.

## Directive reference (syntax summary)

Exact behaviour is documented in the Guide.

| Directive | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `[[pause N]]` | N-second pause |
| `[[sfx name]]` / `[[sfx name N]]` | Play a sound effect (a `.ogg` file) |
| `[[fx name(...)]]` | Call an engine effect function (phone buzz, knock, bamf, …) |
| `[[set key]]` / `[[set key = value]]` | Scene-local state |
| `[[if expr]]` / `[[elif expr]]` / `[[else]]` / `[[/if]]` | Conditional |
| `[[label name]]` | Anchor for `[[goto]]` |
| `[[goto name]]` | Jump to a label in the scene |
| `[[choice]]` / `= option` / `[[/choice]]` | Player choice |
| `[[call scene_id]]` | Chain another scene |
| `[[show Character …]]` / `[[hide Character]]` | Visual change without dialogue |
| `[[phone open]]` / `[[phone open Character]]` / `[[phone close]]` | Phone UI |
| `[[mod_set ...]]` | Persistent state change (only allowlisted operations) |
| `[[approval Char love\|trust ±N]]` | Move love/trust by a stat tier (`tiny_stat` ... `massive_stat`) or integer (≥ 1) |

## Expression grammar (inside `[[if]]`)

Allowed:

- Comparisons: `==`, `!=`, `<`, `<=`, `>`, `>=`
- Logic: `and`, `or`, `not`
- Literals: int, float, str (`"..."`), `True`, `False`, `None`
- Attribute access on allowlisted roots: `<Character>.attr`,
  `player.attr`, or a scene-local state key
- Membership: `x in y`, `x not in y`
- Parentheses for grouping

Not allowed:

- Arithmetic (`+`, `-`, `*`, `/`)
- Function calls, unless the function is in
  `_allowlists/condition_functions.yaml`
- f-strings, lambdas, comprehensions, slicing, indexing

## Keeping this file fresh

Run `Tools/Generate-Cheatsheet.ps1` whenever the mod adds a new
mood, face, location, SFX, or interpolation path. The script reads
every YAML under `scenes_source/_allowlists/` and rewrites this
document in place.

Never edit this file by hand. If a value is missing, fix the
allowlist YAML and regenerate.
